  "prompt": "How should I proceed after I upgrade my townhall to level 6?",
  "response": "Congratulations on reaching Town Hall 6! This is a significant milestone, unlocking a lot of new potential. Here's a prioritized approach to your progression after upgrading to TH6:\n\n**I. Immediate Actions (Right After Upgrade):**\n\n*   **Builder Priority (Highest to Lowest):**\n    1.  **Laboratory:** This is the **absolute highest priority**. Upgrading your laboratory allows you to start researching higher-level troops, which are crucial for attacking. You want this running constantly.\n    2.  **New Buildings:** Place any new buildings you can afford, even if you can't upgrade them yet. This includes:\n        *   **Wizard Tower (2):** They are extremely useful for defense.\n        *   **Air Defense (2):** Crucial as you'll be facing more air attacks, especially Balloons.\n        *   **Giant Bomb (1):** Excellent for surprise attacks on attacking troops.\n        *   **Walls:** Additional wall sections are vital for protecting your base.\n    3.  **Army Camps (4):** Increasing your army size is *huge* for your attack power. Upgrade these as soon as possible.\n    4.  **Spell Factory:** Start upgrading the Spell Factory as soon as you have enough Elixir.\n    5.  **Clan Castle:** Getting higher-level troops from clan mates can significantly boost your attack and defense.\n    6.  **Collectors and Mines:** While not as immediately impactful as offensive upgrades, maxing your resource collectors and mines is still a good long-term goal.\n\n**II. Upgrade Strategy:**\n\n1.  **Offense, Offense, Offense:**\n    *   **Laboratory Upgrades:** Focus on these in this order:\n        *   **Giants:** A staple for TH6 attacks.\n        *   **Archers:** A versatile and useful troop.\n        *   **Balloons:** Excellent for air attacks, but require good Air Defense knowledge.\n        *   **Healer:** Can be effective if you have the knowledge to protect it.\n        *   **Barbarians:** Always useful for clean-up and tanking.\n        *   **Wall Breakers:** Essential for funneling troops.\n    *   **Army Camps:** Max them out to increase army capacity.\n    *   **Clan Castle:** Upgrade as resources permit for larger troop donations.\n\n2.  **Defense:**\n    *   **Wizard Towers:** Max them out for their powerful splash damage.\n    *   **Air Defenses:** A must to protect against air attacks.\n    *   **Mortars:** Provide splash damage against hordes of troops.\n    *   **Archer Towers:** Solid all-around defense.\n    *   **Cannons:** Effective against ground troops.\n    *   **Traps (Bombs, Spring Traps):** Upgrade these to maximize their effectiveness.\n    *   **Walls:** Get all your walls to at least level 6 (purple). Level 7 (gold) is a good goal.\n\n3.  **Resource Production:**\n    *   **Collectors and Mines:** Keep upgrading these, but they're a lower priority than offense and defense.\n\n**III. Farming Strategy:**\n\n*   **Trophy Range:** Aim for around 1000-1300 trophies. This range usually has a good amount of abandoned bases with full collectors.\n*   **Attack Composition:**\n    *   **Barch (Barbarians/Archers):** A cheap and effective composition for collector raids.\n    *   **Giants/Healers/Archers:** A good strategy to learn, especially for bases with poorly placed air defenses.\n    *   **Giants/Wall Breakers/Archers/Goblins:** Use wallbreakers to break open the base and quickly get to resources.\n*   **Target Selection:**\n    *   **Look for abandoned bases:** Full collectors are a goldmine. Check the collector levels. If they look full, they probably are!\n    *   **Avoid heavily defended bases:** You want quick and easy raids to maximize your farming efficiency.\n\n**IV. Base Design:**\n\n*   **Protect Your Resources:** Design your base to protect your Town Hall.\n*   **Centralized Air Defenses:** Protect them from being easily taken out by air attacks.\n*   **Strategic Trap Placement:** Place traps in locations where troops are likely to path.\n*   **Funneling:** Design your base to guide enemy troops into traps and defenses.\n*   **Compartments:** Break up your base into smaller compartments to slow down attackers.\n\n**V. Key Considerations for TH6:**\n\n*   **Clan Involvement:** Join an active clan that can donate high-level troops and provide advice. This is *invaluable*.\n*   **Donation Strategy:** Donate as often as you can. It helps your clan and earns you experience.\n*   **War Strategy:** At TH6, focusing on funneling Giants into the base to get to the Air Defenses is important.\n\n**Specific TH6 Attack Strategies to Learn:**\n\n*   **Giant/Healer/Archer:** This is a classic TH6 strategy.  Tank with Giants, heal them, and use Archers for support and clean-up.\n*   **Giant/Balloons:** If you see a base with poorly placed Air Defenses, Balloons can wreak havoc.  Use Giants to draw fire, then deploy Balloons behind them.\n*   **Barch/Goblin Knife:** A cheaper, faster option for raiding abandoned bases.\n\n**Important Tips:**\n\n*   **Don't Rush:** Upgrade everything to max level before upgrading to TH7. Rushing can set you back in the long run.\n*   **Be Patient:** Progress takes time. Enjoy the journey!\n*   **Watch Videos:** There are tons of great Clash of Clans strategy videos on YouTube that can help you improve your game.\n*   **Learn from Your Mistakes:** Analyze your attacks and defenses to identify areas where you can improve.\n\nBy following these steps, you'll be well on your way to dominating at Town Hall 6! Good luck and have fun!\n",
